The paper deals with the construction and analysis of binary linear codes, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), consumer electronics and communications (cs.CC), and discrete structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the weight distribution of the codes, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI).
